{"id": "117335", "block": {"feedback_wrong": "", "tests_archive": null, "text": "<p>Along side the <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-blue\">Union-by-Size</span></b> method, there is also a \"<span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\"><b>Union-by-Height</b></span>\" method. In the \"<span class=\"wysiwyg-color-green\"><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\">Union-by-Height</span></b></span>\" method, the sentinel node of the\u00a0<i>shorter</i>\u00a0set (i.e., smaller height) gets attached to the sentinel node of the\u00a0<i>taller</i> set. Again, ties can be broken arbitrarily. <br></p><p>Let's say we start with this disjoint set:</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ucarecdn.com/868f9d91-01ca-4d90-9949-36e1cf4baa90/\"></p><p>\n\nBelow is the result of performing\u00a0<span class=\"wysiwyg-color-green\"><b>union</b></span>(A, C), but using the <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\">Union-by-Height</span></b>\u00a0approach. The sentinel node of A (which is B) has a height of 3, and the sentinel node of C (which is C) has a height of 2, so the sentinel node of the <i>taller</i> set (B) is made the <i>parent</i>, and the sentinel node of the <i>shorter</i> set (C) is made the <i>child</i>.\n\n</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://ucarecdn.com/e0a777a6-c2e1-4e7a-a676-6bfd1d15f78c/\"><br></p><p>Just like <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-blue\">Union-by-Size</span></b>,\u00a0the <span class=\"wysiwyg-color-green\"><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\">Union-by-Height</span></b></span>\u00a0method results in a worst-case time complexity of\u00a0<b>O(log <i>n</i>) </b>for the \"find\" operation.<br></p><p><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-red\">STOP and Think:</span></b> If I used <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-blue\">Union-by-Size</span></b> instead of <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\">Union-by-Height</span></b> on the example above, would the resulting tree be better, worse, or just as good as the one I got from <b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-purple\">Union-by-Height</span></b>?<br></p>", "subtitle_files": [], "options": {}, "name": "text", "subtitles": {}, "animation": null, "feedback_correct": "", "source": null, "video": null}, "time": "2016-09-04T00:49:16.722064"}